TextEng: I should go.
Who are you?
A reading?
Very well. I'll go.
I have your cards, here.
Anything of value. Cough it up or die, woman.
Text: 가치 있는 거 뭐든지. 내놓든지 죽든지 골라, 여자.

TextEng: Coin would be fine. Or gems, jewels, anything valuable.
Text: 동전이면 좋겠어. 아니면 보석, 장신구, 가치 있는 거 뭐든지.

TextEng: Your valuables for your life. Now that's a fair trade.
Text: 네 귀중품과 네 목숨을 맞바꾸는 거야. 공정한 거래지.

TextEng: I prize gold much more highly.
Alright. But make it good.
Katriana mentioned something about a reading...
Actually, I'd prefer something more substantial as a reward.
Text: 사실, 보상으로 더 실질적인 걸 받고 싶어.

TextEng: Yes, I'd like that.
Perhaps not. But take the cards anyway, they're yours.
Text: 아닐지도. 하지만 어쨌든 카드 가져가, 네 거야.

TextEng: I need no reward. The cards are yours.
Text: 보상은 필요 없어. 카드는 네 거야.

TextEng: I do not believe in your hedge magics.
Text: 네 엉터리 마법 따위 믿지 않아.

TextEng: No. I've no interest in such a thing.
Very well. That's very kind of you.
Whose hands?
That's it? I should cut your throat for giving me that garbage!
Text: 그게 다야? 이따위 헛소리 해주고 목을 베어버려야겠어!

TextEng: Well, thanks for nothing.
Thank you, Daschnaya.
